@startuml BristolWest_Notification_SequenceDiagram

title Bristol West (Farmers Insurance)\nSequence Diagram — Quote Notification Flow\n(After Quote is Published)

skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor   #E6F4EA
  BorderColor       #2E7D32
  FontColor         #1B5E20
  FontStyle         bold
}

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor              #444444
  ArrowFontColor          #444444
  ArrowFontSize           11
  LifeLineBorderColor     #888888
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #F9F9F9
  BoxBackgroundColor      #F5F5F5
  BoxBorderColor          #CCCCCC
  DividerBackgroundColor  #FFF3CC
  DividerBorderColor      #CC9900
  GroupBackgroundColor    #E8EAF6
  GroupBorderColor        #283593
  GroupFontColor          #1A237E
  NoteBackgroundColor     #FFFDE7
  NoteBorderColor         #F9A825
}

skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor   #DDEEFF
  BorderColor       #336699
  FontColor         #003366
}

' ─────────────────────────────
' PARTICIPANTS
' ─────────────────────────────
participant "Quote\nService"        as QS   #E6F4EA
participant "Kafka\nquote-generated\n:9092" as KAFKA #E8EAF6
participant "Notification\nService" as NS   #E6F4EA
participant "Email\n(Spring Mail)"  as MAIL #FFF3CC
participant "SMTP Server"           as SMTP #F3E5F5
actor       "Customer"              as CUST #DDEEFF

' ─────────────────────────────
' DIVIDER — starting point
' ─────────────────────────────
== Quote Persisted to DB (starting point) ==

' ─────────────────────────────
' PHASE 1 — Publish Event
' ─────────────────────────────
== Phase 1 : Publish Quote Event ==

QS   -> QS   : Build QuoteGeneratedEvent\n(quoteId, quoteNumber, customerName,\ncustomerEmail, coverageType,\ntotalPremium, expiresAt)

QS   -> KAFKA : publish(QuoteGeneratedEvent)\ntopic: quote-generated

note right of KAFKA
  Message serialized
  as JSON via
  KafkaTemplate
end note

KAFKA --> QS  : ack (offset committed)

QS   -> QS   : Return QuoteResponseDTO\nto API Gateway → Customer

' ─────────────────────────────
' PHASE 2 — Consume Event
' ─────────────────────────────
== Phase 2 : Consume Quote Event ==

KAFKA -> NS  : deliver QuoteGeneratedEvent\n(consumer group: notification-group)

activate NS

NS   -> NS   : Deserialize JSON\nto QuoteGeneratedEvent

NS   -> NS   : Validate event fields\n(email, quoteNumber, premium)

' ─────────────────────────────
' PHASE 3 — Build & Send Email
' ─────────────────────────────
== Phase 3 : Build & Send Email ==

NS   -> MAIL : buildEmailMessage()\n(to: customerEmail,\nsubject: "Your Bristol West Quote is Ready")

note right of NS
  Email body includes:
  - Quote Number
  - Coverage Type
  - Premium Breakdown
  - Expiry Date (30 days)
  - CTA: "View & Accept Quote"
end note

MAIL -> MAIL : Compose HTML email\nusing template

MAIL -> SMTP : Connect & authenticate\n(host, port, TLS)

SMTP --> MAIL : Connection established

MAIL -> SMTP : Submit email message\n"Your Auto Quote is Ready — BW-YYYY-XXXXXX"

activate CUST

SMTP -> CUST  : Deliver email to inbox

' ─────────────────────────────
' PHASE 4 — Confirmation
' ─────────────────────────────
== Phase 4 : Confirmation ==

CUST --> SMTP : Email delivered

SMTP --> MAIL : 250 OK

MAIL --> NS   : Send success

NS   -> NS   : Log: "Notification sent\nfor quoteId={id}"

deactivate NS

CUST -> CUST : Opens email\nReviews quote summary

deactivate CUST

note over CUST
  Customer sees:
  Quote #, Premium,
  Coverage details &
  "Accept Quote" link
end note

@enduml
